-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
0. What is it?
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

PyCMBS (Python Cloud Message Brokering Service): A Python implementation of a Message Brokering Service for Cloud

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. The Latest Version
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

version 0.1
13 March 2012
status: Still an ongoing work

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. API Documentation
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
the api documentation are available through this html file:
 PyCMBS/pycmbs/doc/index.html

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Installation
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

3.1. Requirements
-----------------
This software needs this packages to run:
* python == 2.7
* python-all-dev
* python-setuptools (to execute the setup.py file)
* python-zmq (The ZMQ library)
* pyocni ( https://github.com/jordan-developer/PyOCNI )
* couchdb >= 1.2.0 (Easiest install: using build-couchdb https://github.com/iriscouch/build-couchdb )
   To test CouchDB:          http://127.0.0.1:5984
   To test the CouchDB GUI:  http://127.0.0.1:5984/_utils/

3.2. Install
------------
sudo python setup.py install

3.3. Configuration
------------------

Logger configuration:    Logging.conf
PyCMBS configuration:    pycmbs.conf

